{"lemma":"أَنِيسٌ","slug":"أَنِيسٌ","root":"#.ن.س","root_slug":"_-ن-س","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ن-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1348"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B3%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"close, intimate; close friend; friendly, kind, affable, civil, polite, courteous"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Anis"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb أَنُسَ (ʔanusa)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.niːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1348","headword_ar":"اَنِيسٌ","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^aAnisN","text_ar":"مُوَانِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally used as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sociable, companionable, conversable, friendly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"familiar, person; a cheerful companion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one with whom one is sociable, companionable, conversable, friendly, familiar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by whose company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"converse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"presence, one is cheered, gladdened, solaced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consoled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA biAld~aAri A^niyso","text_ar":"مَا بِالدَّارِ انِيسْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or, as in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^aniysK","text_ar":"مِنْ اَنِيسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in the house any one by whose company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"converse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"presence, one is cheered, gladdened, solaced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consoled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is not in the house any one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=nisapN","text_ar":"ا=نِسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aniysu","text_ar":"الاَنِيسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The domestic cock;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uqaru","text_ar":"الشُّقَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aniysapu","text_ar":"الاَنِيسَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^onuwsapu","text_ar":"مَاْنُوسَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [imperfectly decl., being a proper name and of the fem. gender,] (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA^onuwsapu","text_ar":"المَاْنُوسَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) of which [says ISd] I know no verb: (M:) because, when a man sees it in the night, he becomes cheerful and tranquil thereat, even if it be in a desert land. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAtati AlA^aniysapu","text_ar":"بَاتَتِ الاَنِيسَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aniysatahu","text_ar":"اَنِيسَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire was during night his cheerful companion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his cheerer by its presence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%B3/","headword_ar":"أنيسون","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=49896#0ec19b","body_html":"أنيسون: آنسون، ولم تضبط الكلمة في معجم فريتاج، وأَنيسون في محيط المحيط، واحدته انسونة وفي معجم فوك: أنَيْسون، والعامة تقول يانسون (محيط المحيط)."}]}}